{
  "stem": "17761.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 80.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] After the Ribbentrop-Molotov Pact--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was a few days-- the end-- the 23 or something of August, 1939, in which they divided Poland, which was later a few days invaded by the Germans and then invaded from the other side by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They divided Poland.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They also [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] did something to the territories of Romania.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Romania between the two wars, between the First and the Second World War, called Great Romania, had also-- included also Bukovina and Bessarabia.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Bessarabia was Russian-speaking.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Bukovina was German-speaking.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Bessarabia they took from the Russian and Bukovina from the Austria-Hungarian empire, so these two regions belong to Romania.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "According to the Ribbentrop-Molotov Pact, this we think so, northern Romania, with its capital Tschernowitz, went over to Russia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And southern Bukovina remained Romania.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Our little place, Vatra-Dornei, as well as Arbore and Balaceana, they belonged to southern Romania, so we remained under Romania rule until we were deported.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But in 1941, in June, 1941, when the Germans invaded Russia, the Romanians became their allies and they went with them into Russia.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So it was somehow a combination of German and-- and Romanian administration, where the Germans determined what the Romanians have to do.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "After the front went far into Russia, going close to Moscow, the area between the Dniester and the Bug called Transnistria, that means over the Dniester, was given to the Romanian that they should rule it, again under the same conditions that the German had the superior domination.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the Romanian, they were directly involved into that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In any case, but the thousand part, they were all communities who continue to live under the-- the war conditions in the-- in our places.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
